<item>
            <title>[SEC-2548] AuthenticationSwitchUserEvent is published before the actual Authentication object is placed in SecurityContext</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2548</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The AuthenticationSwitchUserEvent is published in &lt;tt&gt;attemptSwitchUser&lt;/tt&gt; method before the Authentication object is placed in the Security Context. The event should be published after line 158 where &lt;tt&gt;SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(targetUser);&lt;/tt&gt; is called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue is also there when trying to exit an user, The event is published in &lt;tt&gt;attemptExitUser&lt;/tt&gt; when it should be published in the &lt;tt&gt;doFilter&lt;/tt&gt; method after line  173.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
